      <description>As the world’s third largest donor of foreign aid, the U.K. may be tempted to follow a European trend of using aid funds to pay for hosting refugees, but Aston University’s Balazs Szent-Ivanyi argues that doing so could harm the country’s long-term interests.  </description>
